==Tandy==
===Tandy Color Computer 3===
The Tandy Color Computer 3 could display all of the modes of the Tandy Color Computer 1 and 2, except the Semigraphics modes, plus resolutions of 160, 256, 320, or 640 pixels wide by 192 to 225 lines from a palette of 64 colors. The 320 mode allowed 16 simultaneous colors, while the 640 mode allowed 4.
:{| | [[Image:TandyCoCo3 Mode320x192x16 palette sample image.jpg]] | [[Image:TandyCoCo3 Mode320x192x16 palette color test chart.png]] |}
==Thomson== For [[Thomson SA|Thomson computers]], a popular brand in France, the most common display modes are 320×200, with 8×1 attribute cells with 2 colours. The [[Thomson TO7]] can only display the 8 "saturated" colors. The [[Thomson TO7/70]] and [[Thomson MO5]] have the 16 color palette shown below as a fixed palette (just like on C64 or MSX1). On later models, these 16 colours can be chosen from 4096 and other video modes are available, removing the block constraints but reducing either the color count or the horizontal resolution.
